<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-01-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-01-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="780" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5856.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-14T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1913—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Denver</hi> has been ordered to-day to proceed
                            at once to Acapulco and will arrive there on or about 21st instant.</p>
                        <p>Lay the situation before the Mexican Foreign Office and inform that
                            office of the arrival of the <hi rend="italic">Denver.</hi>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>